		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">tepples wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Is there a language without retarded quirks?</div>
<br />The quirks are probably there because people tried to establish rules to explain things that were created without rules in the first place. Languages are a certain way because people speak that way, so the day someone steps up and decides to dictate what's correct and what's not, they will only be able to create rules if they create tons of exceptions to go along.

		

